RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 59. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RUSSIAN ALPHABET was bumped lightly just after the break but unhindered in making the lead, dueled inside a rival but racing just off the rail, edged clear by the three-eighths, held sway with mild urging through the lane. LUKE ATTACK bumped lightly with a rival at the start, tracked the dueling leaders inside a rival but off the fence, came out in upper stretch in range of the leader but could make no headway. GUST OF WIND was bumped into a rival while bobbling and then was shuffled back just after the start, drifted out early, moved back nearer inside for the turn trailing the field, swung six wide into upper stretch and finished well. WICKED SUPRISE was bumped into a rival after the start, pursued from inside off the leaders, saved ground but failed to rally. ROCKET MAN ATTACK bumped with the outside rival then veered into the inside foe at the start, dueled outside the winner two to three wide for three furlongs, could not kick on. LIGHTNING CASHES stalked the leading pair from outside a rival three to four wide, came up empty and faded in the stretch.

ENTRY.COMMENT: light bump after brk, duel inside, clear by 3/8, mild urging

SUNDAY MISCHIEF was moderately coaxed forward from the start to set the pace in the clear racing off the rail, faced pressure on the turn, was outkicked but second best. RACE.FOOTNOTES: FIRST SQUADRON set the pace in the clear, widened into the turn racing in the two path through that bend and drifting out a bit turning for home, held off a late challenge by ARCH FLYER, who broke inwardly a bit, tracked from inside, saved ground and kept on in the lane to close the gap. PRANCIPANTS raced last but one off the inside going in the three path on the turn, gained show honors inside LADY ATLANTIC, who pursued the eventual winner three wide, could not kick on. NEXT TIME YOU WIN broke inwardly brushing a rival, chased from outside four to five wide, failed to rally. PRINCESS CONSUELA was brushed and had to steady at the start, raced off the inside four to five wide on the turn, failed to menace.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: OPALINE broke inwardly bumping a rival, moved up to press the leader outside three wide, took a narrow lead by upper stretch, lugged in just past the furlong marker when receiving a right-handed use of the crop then forged clear under steady urging. KEEP LEFT broke through the gate but under hold by the assistant starter, was led back around the gate and reloaded, broke outwardly lightly brushing a rival but moved forward to set the pace, soon faced pressure by the eventual winner from outside, was no match and yielded in the stretch. MISS MIA chased from outside mostly four to five wide, went evenly and failed to rally. JEMEZ FALLS was bumped and in tight at the start, chased the leaders from just off the rail, moved out four wide passing the five-sixteenths, ran on evenly.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: FOLLOW THE SIGNS switched outside the pacesetter early, advanced on that one two to three wide on the turn, struck a narrow lead in upper stretch, edged clear and held under steady handling. CHICKS FOR FREE angled in early racing off the pace, advanced inside rivals but just off the rail late on the turn, kept on in the stretch to get up for second late over CRANKSHAFT, who moved clear and shifted in to set the pace inside, could not kick on with the winner and lost place late. TIME HEIST was in tight and altered outside rivals early, raced toward the rear off the rail and improved position in the stretch. RACE.FOOTNOTES: SOVIET STANDARD got away alertly and moved clear to set the pace racing just off the rail, was given right-handed encouragement in mid-stretch then lugged out near the sixteenth pole under left-handed use of the crop, just lasted. BEEASY stalked from outside three to four wide, steadied and was forced out near the sixteenth pole, was gaining willingly late. TIZWOW was under hold late up the backstretch pursuing the pace, failed to rally. DASTARDLY DEEDS broke a step slowly and lacked early speed, failed to rally while racing off the inside. RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUST A WONDER moved forward soon after the start to press from outside three to four wide, dueled in upper stretch, edged clear coming to the sixteenth pole and just lasted from STOPSHOPPINGAMY, who shifted in early after being in just slightly tight quarters, saved ground inside on the turn, angled out about the eighth pole for room, was gaining fast but too late. ISABELLACANNETELLA chased from inside steadied slightly entering the turn, lost ground on the leader through the stretch and was in just a bit tight late. WAY TOO SMARTE was off the pace racing three to five wide through the turn coming into the stretch six deep and needed more. GHAALEB'S DOMAIN switched out and chased from the three to four path just off the leading trio through the turn, came up empty for the stretch. FOLLOWING AN OBJECTION BY THE TRAINER OF ISABELLACANNETELLA AGAINST LIPLINER ALLEGING INTERFERENCE, NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.
